(power_pad, time).explanation: Power consumption of I/O pads does not directly influence processor execution time, as timing is primarily determined by critical path delays in the core logic rather than pad power characteristics;

(power_pad, area_net_area).explanation: The net area requirements in a processor design determine the number and complexity of I/O pads needed, which subsequently affects the power consumption of those pads;

(power_pad, area_cell_area).explanation: Larger cell areas in processor designs typically require more extensive I/O infrastructure and pad resources, leading to increased pad power consumption;
